2.00	Chenganoor_Raman_Pillai	Chenganoor Raman Pillai	Guru Chenganoor Raman Pillai, also spelt Chengannur Raman Pillai, (1886-1980) was a celebrated Kathakali artist from Kerala in south India. He was known for his brilliant portrayal of the anti-heroic Kathi roles on stage, and was a palace dancer to the Travancore Maharaja in a career spanning almost 65 years.	
